## Round 6 addendum (review comments applied stack-wide)
Two review comments asked for consistency: 'Why do you need this
[client_is_clickhouse] check? Don't we already skip NOT CLICKHOUSE BACKEND
above?' and 'shouldn't this [isinstance fixture check] use the NOT
CLICKHOUSE check?'. Applied across every change in the stack:
- test_calls_complete.py / test_otel_calls_complete.py: wholly
  ClickHouse-only files -> module-level pytestmark =
  pytest.mark.skipif(NOT_CLICKHOUSE_BACKEND, ...); their
  clickhouse_trace_server fixtures reverted to plain asserts (unreachable
  on the fake).
- test_ttl_insert_paths.py: the four raw-read tests carry the skipif
  decorator; internal_server fixture reverted to an assert. The
  endpoints round-trip test keeps running on the fake.
- conftest ch_server: checks get_trace_server_flag(request) !=
  'clickhouse' (the authority the skipif string mirrors) instead of
  isinstance, then asserts the type.
- test_call_lifecycle.py: a gate the earlier conversion script MISSED
  (it died on file_storage before reaching it) is now a decorator.
- test_client_trace dupe-select: split in two — the output-shape
  assertions run on every backend; a new
  test_calls_query_dupe_select_columns_no_duplicate_sql carries the
  skipif and asserts the emitted SQL. GOTCHA: get_calls returns a LAZY
  iterator — the new test must consume it (len(list(calls))) or no
  query executes and the log assertion IndexErrors (caught on the CH
  run).
- client_is_clickhouse(client) now has exactly ONE user: the
  force_merge_calls helper in test_call_stats (a capability no-op on a
  live client instance, not a test gate — markers cannot express it).

## Errors & Mistakes (round 6)
- A gt track invocation had left HEAD on andrew/fake-ts-01-skeleton; the
  review edits and several test runs silently ran against the SKELETON
